Refactor `NNTreeImpl::withinLimits`: use `const` references for parameters, simplify `withinLimits` logic, and improve code readability with subscript operators.
Refactor `NNTree::deepen`: introduce lambda for failure handling, simplify loop logic, and replace redundant code with subscript operators.
Refactor `NNTree::remove`: simplify logic, replace `getArrayItem` and `getArrayNItems` with subscript operators, introduce `std::cmp` utilities, and remove redundant debug traces.
Refactor `NNTreeIterator::insertAfter`: use `const` references for parameters, replace `getArrayNItems` with `size`, and improve error handling logic.

issue.title: [Server Issue]: Oritech mod floods debug.log with excessive network entity updates

labels.name: Status: Needs Confirmation
labels.description: Don't know if this issue is valid yet

issue.body:
### Modpack Version

1.0.2

### Describe the issue

**Description:**
The Oritech mod generates an extreme amount of DEBUG-level logging for machine network updates. With just a few machines running, debug.log grows over 100MB within hours due to constant messages like:

```
[17-8-2025 21:59:53.075] [Server thread/DEBUG] [oritech/]: sending networked entity update: TICK at BlockPos{x=4008, y=72, z=-56} for oritech:refinery_entity
[17-8-2025 21:59:53.174] [Server thread/DEBUG] [oritech/]: sending networked entity update: SPARSE_TICK at BlockPos{x=4040, y=72, z=-40} for oritech:foundry_entity
```

**Impact:**
1. Debug.log grows at unsustainable rates (~50MB/hour per few machines)
2. Makes server log files completely unmanageable
3. Obscures other important debug information
4. Causes performance issues when writing logs
5. Makes log sharing impossible for troubleshooting

comment.body:
> You should report this upstream

Thanks for the suggestion! I’ve submitted this issue upstream to the Oritech repository ([Issue #521](https://github.com/Rearth/Oritech/issues/521)). Hopefully, they can address the excessive DEBUG logging in a future update.
